<Title>Thrust Reverser Blocker Door Hinge Covers</Title>
<DispatchCondition>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>
<Effectivities>
<Effectivity>For GE Engines:</Effectivity>
</Effectivities>Up to thirteen may be missing.  Twelve may be missing from one engine and one may be missing from the other engine.</Para>
<Para>
<Effectivities>
<Effectivity>For GE Engines:</Effectivity>
</Effectivities>For each missing thrust reverser blocker door hinge cover, the corresponding thrust reverser blocker door (CDL item 78-31-01) must also be removed.</Para>
<Para>
<Effectivities>
<Effectivity>For GE Engines:</Effectivity>
</Effectivities>If blocker hinge covers are missing from both engines, determine the performance limited weight adjustments for each engine and then combine the results.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>For more than one blocker door missing from one engine, the airplane must be dispatched using MEL item 78-31-01.</Para>
</Note>
